      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Muslim Hands Inc demonstrates high organizational maturity, having <cite id=\"1\">operated for over 30 years</cite>. Their financial health is marked by a <cite id=\"14\">working capital ratio of 26.3 months</cite> according to some metrics, which is far above the industry standard. This is complemented by a <cite id=\"15\">Silver Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, indicating a commitment to public disclosure. Furthermore, their <cite id=\"16\">cost per beneficiary is calculated at $46.79</cite>, which is considered exceptional for complex humanitarian interventions in conflict zones."
      ],
      "summary": "Muslim Hands Inc is a humanitarian organization that has been operating since <cite id=\"1\">its founding in 1993</cite>, focusing on disaster relief and sustainable development. The organization reported <cite id=\"2\">$452,623 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, representing a significant <cite id=\"3\">3-year revenue CAGR of 69.0%</cite>. Their operations are diverse, ranging from the <cite id=\"4\">Gaza Emergency Appeal</cite> to the <cite id=\"5\">Safe Water Fund</cite>, providing both immediate relief and long-term infrastructure in regions such as <cite id=\"6\">Yemen, Pakistan, and Mali</cite>. While the organization maintains <cite id=\"7\">100% independent board members</cite>, it currently holds an <cite id=\"8\">overall score of 71.0/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>. A key differentiator for the charity is its <cite id=\"9\">15.2 months of working capital</cite>, which provides a substantial buffer for emergency response. Despite this stability, the organization faces challenges with its <cite id=\"10\">program expense ratio of 35.3%</cite> as reported by third-party evaluators, which is significantly lower than the <cite id=\"11\">peer program ratio median of 89.8%</cite> for the humanitarian sector.",
